Kubernetes Client Integration

library. Also, updates the documentation to fill out more of the basic
usage patterns and functionality.

v1.1.1

Improved version management functionality
and adds v1.15 API support.

v1.2.0

Refined module importing, added metadata to library versions, expanded
documentation, and cleaned up resource initialization.

v1.2.1

Generalized version definitions that allow for `KubernetesVersion`
objects to be used anywhere a Kubernetes version argument exists.
Adds convenience functions for loading access configs and retrieving
version information from the remote cluster.

ConfigMap Example

Adds an example of how to configure a ConfigMap resource.

v1.2.2

Rbac authorization cleanup.

v1.2.3

Adds convenience functions for parsing and loading multi-document
YAML files into Resource lists and into bundles.

v1.2.4

- Adds `ResourceBundle.remove()` function.
- Initial unit testing.
- Fixes coordination API client specification.

v.1.2.5

- Expanded multi-resource handling in the ResourceBundle class.
- Updated documentation.

v.1.3.0

- Implemented CLI command interface for bundled operations.
- Enhanced CRUD bundling operations to include optional display
  output as well as restructured the return type to include more
  information from the API.
- Fixed `IntOrString` data type handling due to limitations in the
  OpenApi v2 type handling that was causing incorrect but unavoidable
  validation errors.
- Updated to latest minor Kubernetes API versions.

v.1.3.1

- Enhanced CLI for bundled operations, including a new `invoke`
  operation that allows for custom configuration based on
  user-defined arguments.
- Fixed error code displays during bundle creation due to a
  namespace not existing in the cluster.
- Expanded documentation around CLI usage.

Documentation

Updated README.md to match recent changes in the documentation
resources.

Documentation

Code example cleanup on the main documentation pages.
Add .gitlab-ci.yml

CI Setup

Populate the CI settings for unit testing with
pytest.

CI Display

Add badges and tweak settings for unit testing
from CI.

v1.3.2

- Expanded unit testing of recently added functionality.
- Fixes in-cluster configuration in `kuber.load_access_configs()`.
- Cleanup to inline code documentation in multiple modules.
- Add examples to documentation.

v1.4.0

- Complete unit testing to 100% coverage.
- Refactors the `cli` package to the `interface` package.
- Cleanup to inline code documentation in multiple modules.
- Add bundling with CLI example to documentation.
- Add documentation on how Kubernetes version handling works.

v1.5.0

- Adds settings object to bundles for managing input
  configuration settings alongside bundles from the CLI.
- Refactors the `management` module into a subpackage for
  cleaner organization of internal structure.

v1.5.0

- Adds settings object to bundles for managing input
  configuration settings alongside bundles from the CLI.
- Refactors the `management` module into a subpackage for
  cleaner organization of internal structure.

CI Enhancements

Expand CI to include multiple python versions and a docs
build test.

v1.5.1

- Updates to v1.15 to `alpha.1`.
- Fixes api execution namespace issue when managing
  namespaces.
- Adds resource targeting to the CLI interface for
  partial bundle management.
- Bundle settings can now be serialized to dicts or YAML
  strings for external use.

v1.6.0

- Flattened the vendored dependencies to make all
  available as modules within a particular version
  package.
- Added correct type management for `Quantity` data
  type properties.
- Fixed null handling in `IntOrString` types.
- Corrected default namespace handling in bundle CRUD
  operations so that explicit namespaces are not
  overridden.
- Added unit test for vendored dependency to ensure
  proper parsing.

v1.6.1

- Added `ResourceBundle.from_directory_files()` that allow
  for specifying files within a directory to load and the order
  in which they will be loaded. Very useful for configurations
  where the order of application is important and resources are
  spread out across multiple files.
- Added `kuber.from_directory()` that mirrors the above function
  to expose that to the bundle creation process.

v1.6.2

- Fixed parsing errors in the `apiregistration` modules.
- Enforce resource namespace prioritization in CLI invocations.
- Update 1.12.x branch.

v1.6.3

- Changed pyyaml Loader behavior to use Loader by default instead of
  CLoader for greater compatibility.
- Added a top-level module variable to allow users to override pyaml
  Loader if desired.

v1.7.0

- Adds dynamic filtering/accessing to the `ResourceBundle.resources`
  object using a custom class instead of returning a tuple.
- Explicitly sets flow style to be block instead of inline when
  serializing resources to yaml.
- Makes unix-style line endings consistent across development platforms.

v1.7.1

- Fixes recursion error caused by the JSONSchemaProps definition,
  which has a `not` property that is also a JSONSchemaProps object.
  The new behavior is to detect recursive properties during the
  generation process and default those to `None` instead of
  constructing the definition object.
- Updates v1.11 to 1.11.10.

v1.7.2

- Fixes missing `apiVersion` and/or `kind` properties on non-resource
  object creation that reference other values as opposed to their own
  api version or kind.
- Updates v1.13 to 1.13.6.
- Updates v1.15 and pre to v1.15.0-alpha.3.

v1.7.3

- Increased compatibility with serialized Kubernetes Python client
  library values, which will sometimes serialize to snake case
  values instead of camelCase ones.

v1.7.4

- Increased compatibility with Kubernetes variable names that don't
  follow strict camelCase format and require case-insensitive
  comparison to guarantee mapping between camel and snake case
  representations via intermediate states like the Kubernetes
  Python client.
- Exposes status objects on supported resources.

v1.8.0

- Added `ResourceBundle.new()` function for creating resources, adding
  them to the bundle and then returning them for immediate
  configuration.
- Added `.keys()`, `.values()` and `.items()` to the bundles settings
  object to make it more compatible with `dict` operations.
- Updated v1.14 and v1.15 to latest versions.
- Introduces v1.16 and changes _pre_ to target 1.16.

v1.8.2

1.15 stable release update, with patch updates to 1.12, 1.13 and 1.14
as well.

v1.9.0

Adds a `get_containers()` function to all resources that have
a container spec to make it easy to iterate through containers
without having to dig into the hierarchy or know the names of
the containers.

Also includes the following API updates:
  - v1.17: 0.0.0 -> 1.17.0-alpha.0
  - v1.16: 1.16.0-alpha.2 -> 1.16.0-beta.1
  - v1.15: 1.15.1 -> 1.15.3
  - v1.14: 1.14.4 -> 1.14.6
  - v1.13: 1.13.8 -> 1.13.10
  - pre: 1.16.0-alpha.2 -> 1.17.0-alpha.0
  - latest: 1.15.1 -> 1.15.3

v1.9.1

Fixes `false` boolean key/value pairs when serializing resources
for output.

v1.10.0

Fixes `0` integer values from being dropped during IO operations
and upgrades to the latest versions of Kubernetes libraries.

v1.10.1

Update to latest kubernetes versions and patches.

Fuzzy Filtering

Add fuzzy resource filtering to
ResourceArrays and modify CLI targeting
to use the fuzzy resource filtering
instead of exact matching for targets.

Job Template Containers

Fix the parsing of container paths for `get_containers`
that reference a job_template. Also, update versions to:

v0.13.0

- Updates and refactors repository for black, flake8 and mypy compliance.
- Replaces setup.py with poetry for package and dependency management and
  adds task runners to simplify repetitive tasks.
- Introduces experimental helm upstream bundling support such that bundles
  can be created from rendering a helm template to more easily integrate
  helm 3 charts into the kuber bundle management process.

v0.13.1

- Increases path specification flexibility be handling
  pathlib.Path in more ResourceBundle methods.
- Fixes experimental helm update command.
- Bumps patch on Kubernetes apis 1.17, 1.18, 1.19 and 1.20
- Moves latest to 1.20 now that is has been released.

Badge URL Fix

Updates the Gitlab build badge URL.

v0.13.2

Adds a test render path alias that allows for test
rendering with mock values when desired.

v0.14.0

Adds new methods to ResourceBundles for more
complex resource ordering management.

Also updates Kubernetes APIs to:
  - v1.20: 1.20.0 -> 1.20.1
  - v1.19: 1.19.5 -> 1.19.6
  - v1.18: 1.18.13 -> 1.18.14
  - v1.17: 1.17.15 -> 1.17.16
  - latest: 1.20.0 -> 1.20.1

v0.15.0

Adds transparent support for custom objects
through the new `custom_v1` module and
`CustomObject` class. See documentation for
usage.

v0.15.1

While the Python kubernetes client has issues
with `IntOrString` data types because of their
continued use of OpenAPIV2 schema validation,
we move to make that type available in kuber
to match the expected behavior.

Formatting Updates

Black formatted changes made to non-library files
updated to latest mypy validations.
